reviewText: I received it in record but gave as a gift and did not get any feedback from the recipient.
This is a cool documentary about what cycle racing in the 70s was like. It's gritty and its great, especially the sound of the bike chains whirring around the sprockets...
Old fashioned by todays standards but very well done, good camera angles, well narrated and well edited - the day is well covered and sequential.  I'm surprised it isn't available on DVD yet.
